Muriate of Potassa (Potassane) is a perfectly neutral
body & when six proportions of oxygene are
added to it it still remains neutral. -
Muriatic acid (chlorine & hydrogene) is a strong
acid & according to the relation above
stated it ought not to lose its acid
powers by the addition of six proportions of
oxygene -. Till a pure combination of
Chlorine & oxygene is obtained possessed of
acid properties we have no right to
say [deletion]that in the hyperoxymuriates[/deletion] that
